{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Continuous auto-deploy: the running Gerrit environment reflects `main` without manual deploy or restart\n\n## Why\nLanding a change on `main` does NOT update the running environment: the review-bot container's code,\n`replication.config`, and g2p config need a MANUAL deploy (SSM / setup-*.sh) + sometimes a restart.\nThis drifts + toils (S2's merge-review code landed but the running bot is pre-S2; the S3 replication\nfix was hand-applied). The environment must AUTO-REFLECT `main` — without ever destabilising the\nLIVE, FAIL-CLOSED gate (no LLM-Review vote ⇒ no submit; a bad deploy could freeze all submissions).\n\n## What\n- **Trigger (RESOLVED): on-box systemd timer** `rebar-autodeploy.timer` (2-min) → `.service` oneshot\n  running `infra/scripts/autodeploy.sh`. Chosen over a GitHub-Actions→SSM `deploy.yml` because it adds\n  NO GitHub→AWS trust surface (no OIDC/`ssm:SendCommand` grant that would make the GH runner a\n  lateral-movement path); the box already reads the PUBLIC mirror read-only + has an instance role.\n- **Loop:** `flock -n` guard; fetch `origin/main`; no-op when `== deployed-sha`\n  (`/var/lib/rebar/deployed-sha`, initialised to current HEAD on first run WITHOUT deploying, written\n  atomically only on success). Deploy ONLY the mirror `main` tip (Verified-by-construction: it only\n  advances via Gerrit submit). Change-detect per component via `git diff --name-only\n  deployed-sha..origin/main` ∩ a path manifest (review-bot: src/rebar/**, Dockerfile.reviewbot,\n  pyproject, docker-compose; replication: replication.config; g2p: ini + materialize script).\n- **Apply only what changed (v1 = review-bot ONLY):** review-bot → tag current image `:prev`, sync\n  source (see Box-adaptation), `docker compose build && up -d review-bot`. **replication/g2p AND\n  `refs/meta/config` are DETECT-ONLY in v1** — a change is signalled (`AUTODEPLOY_ERROR`), never\n  auto-applied (their correct apply needs a live-site copy + SSM PAT re-fetch whose failure modes must\n  not sit in the unattended path guarding a fail-closed gate; v2 follow-up). See Box-adaptation §3.\n\n## Stability — live-pipeline safety (load-bearing)\n1. **Bounded blast radius:** never touch the `gerrit` container (explicit `review-bot` service target\n   + a post-deploy assert the gerrit container id is unchanged); never modify `refs/meta/config` (gate\n   labels/rules/ACLs). No Gerrit restart — only the bot container restarts, only on a code change.\n2. **In-flight reviews delayed, not lost:** a restart drops in-flight webhooks, but the existing\n   reconciler-backfill re-reviews them; the post-deploy health check confirms the reconciler is live.\n3. **Self-heal, never freeze the gate:** after `up -d`, an END-TO-END health check (30s timeout —\n   liveness: process up + `/health` 200) gates success; on failure → immediate\n   rollback to `:prev` + `up -d`; deployed-sha NOT advanced. Max frozen window = the health timeout.\n4. **Failure handling = capped exponential backoff, NOT hard-disable** (mature-OSS consensus: Flux\n   retryInterval/backoff; Argo CD retry backoff duration/factor/maxDuration; k8s controller-runtime\n   ItemExponentialFailureRateLimiter 5ms→1000s; systemd v254 RestartSteps/RestartMaxDelaySec):\n   - rollback keeps last-known-good RUNNING; retry the deploy with backoff base 60s, factor 2, cap\n     15m — never auto-disable the loop (a hard-disable strands the env stale until a human acts).\n   - **SHA-keyed reset (Argo CD's rule):** persist last-attempted-SHA + failure count; a NEW\n     `origin/main` tip RESETS the backoff to base (a fix-forward deploys promptly); a known-bad SHA is\n     not re-attempted faster than the cap (no thrash) and is never permanently blacklisted.\n   - **Outer storm guard:** systemd `StartLimitIntervalSec`/`StartLimitBurst` on the RUNNING bot\n     service catches a crash-looping container (→ failed, needs `reset-failed`) — reserved for the\n     pathological case, NOT the primary retry path.\n5. **Config validated before it touches Gerrit:** parse-check replication/g2p config pre-apply; a\n   malformed config is skipped (prior retained) + alarmed. (Belt-and-suspenders to AC below.)\n\n## Defense-in-depth: a CI gate that rejects malformed config (so it never reaches `main`)\n`make config-check` — parse-validate every infra config: `git config -f {replication,project}.config\n--list`; python configparser on the g2p ini template; `docker compose config -q`; `bash -n` on\n`infra/**/*.sh`. Wired into `test.yml` (⇒ runs in `gerrit-verify` ⇒ the `Verified` gate), so a\nmalformed config FAILS CI and can NEVER land on `main` — the auto-deploy never encounters one at\nruntime (the runtime pre-apply check in Stability §5 is the belt-and-suspenders for a direct box edit).\n\n## Observability + back-out\nStructured deploy log (from→to SHA + components) + `rebar/host:deploy_errors` (host-probe grep of an\n`AUTODEPLOY_ERROR` marker, mirroring voter_errors) + a CloudWatch alarm w/ SNS action; the\nbackoff/failure state is alarmed. Back-out: `systemctl disable --now rebar-autodeploy.timer`; the\nmanual path (compose-up.sh / setup-*.sh) is unchanged.\n\n## Scope\nDeploy orchestrator + systemd units + stability guards + the CI config-check + observability/back-out\non the existing compose stack. Reuses the idempotent setup/materialise appliers. refs/meta/config\nauto-apply deferred (detect + signal). No change to gate semantics (S1/S2) or the 88ab flow.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] A post-gate `main` change auto-reflects on the box (no manual action) ≤ 5 min; latency\n      live-measured. Idempotent: a no-change run is a no-op; a change re-applies ONLY the changed\n      component(s) — verified for review-bot code; a replication.config / g2p / refs-meta change emits\n      `AUTODEPLOY_ERROR` and is NOT auto-applied in v1 (detect-only)\n- [ ] review-bot rebuilt/restarted ONLY on a source-set change (docs-only change ⇒ no rebuild); after\n      a code change the running bot reflects it end-to-end (a merge change gets the S2 merge tag)\n- [ ] Blast radius: the `gerrit` container is provably untouched; `refs/meta/config` never\n      auto-modified; no Gerrit restart. project.config changes are detected + signalled, not attempted\n- [ ] Self-heal: a deliberately-broken bot image FAILS the health check ⇒ rollback to `:prev` (gate\n      restored), deployed-sha not advanced (proven live)\n- [ ] Failure backoff: repeated failure uses capped exponential backoff (base 60s→cap 15m), keeps\n      last-known-good running, and a NEW `main` SHA resets the backoff (fix-forward deploys promptly);\n      the loop never auto-disables; the systemd StartLimit storm-guard is in place\n- [ ] CI config-gate: `make config-check` runs in `test.yml`/`gerrit-verify` and FAILS on a\n      deliberately-malformed config (proven) — a malformed config cannot reach `main`\n- [ ] flock serializes overlapping fires; deploy log + `deploy_errors` metric + alarm applied;\n      back-out (disable timer) tested; manual path still works; live end-to-end auto-deploy verified\n\n## Box-adaptation of the deploy mechanism (grounded in live box i-00880b2c7f13527c5)\n\nLive SSM inspection changed two assumptions in v1–v4, so the mechanism is adapted and v1's\n**auto-apply surface is narrowed to the review-bot container only** (config = detect+signal).\nThe safety guarantees (blast radius, self-heal, backoff, config-check-at-CI, flock) are unchanged.\n\n### Observed box facts (SSM)\n- `/opt/rebar` is a plain **copy** of the repo root — NOT a git checkout (no `.git`; uid 502; a\n  `.deployed_ref` marker). It is the compose `build.context` (`../..`) for both services; review-bot\n  bakes source at **build** time (no source bind-mount), so a rebuild picks up new code.\n- Real compose working dir: `/opt/rebar/infra/compose` (services `gerrit`, `review-bot`).\n- The ONLY runtime state under `/opt/rebar` is `infra/compose/.env` (SSM-sourced secrets, git-ignored,\n  0600, regenerated at boot by `fetch-secrets.sh`). All Docker state lives OUTSIDE `/opt/rebar` —\n  named volumes (`gerrit_git`/`gerrit_index`/…) + bind mounts under `/var/gerrit/*` — so a source\n  resync cannot touch it. systemd 252. review-bot health `http://localhost:8000/health` → `{\"status\":\"ok\"}`.\n\n### Adapted mechanism\n1. **Mirror clone (self-bootstrapping).** autodeploy maintains its own **regular** git clone at\n   `MIRROR_DIR=/var/lib/rebar/mirror` — `git clone https://github.com/navapbc/rebar.git` (public HTTPS,\n   no auth; a *regular* clone, NOT `--mirror`/`--bare`, so `origin/main` resolves for the diff/rev-parse\n   ops). autodeploy self-bootstraps it if absent and **aborts if the remote is not `https://`** (supply-\n   chain guard). ALL git ops — fetch `--prune`, `rev-parse origin/main`, the\n   `git diff --name-only deployed..target` component change-detection, checkout of the target — run there.\n2. **Source sync = `rsync -a --delete $MIRROR_DIR/ /opt/rebar/`** with hard excludes protecting runtime\n   state: `--exclude '/.git'`, `--exclude 'infra/compose/.env'`, `--exclude '/.deployed_ref'`, plus the\n   dev/state set (`.venv .terraform .serena .claude .tickets-tracker`). `.env` + Docker volumes are never\n   touched; ownership kept 502:502.\n3. **Apply — review-bot ONLY (v1 narrowed).** On a review-bot source-set change\n   (`src/rebar/** infra/compose/Dockerfile.reviewbot infra/compose/docker-compose.yml pyproject.toml`):\n   tag current image `:prev` (guarded — skip if none, first-build has no rollback target), `docker compose\n   build review-bot && up -d review-bot` in `/opt/rebar/infra/compose`, END-TO-END health-gate (liveness:\n   process up + `/health` 200), rollback to `:prev` on failure, blast-radius assert (gerrit container id\n   unchanged), `docker image prune -f`. **replication.config, g2p, and refs/meta/config are DETECT-ONLY in\n   v1** — a change is signalled (`AUTODEPLOY_ERROR` marker) for a manual operator apply, never auto-applied.\n   Rationale: their correct apply needs live-site copy (`/var/gerrit/site/etc/…`) and an SSM PAT re-fetch\n   (`materialize-g2p-config.sh`) whose failure modes should not sit in the unattended path guarding a\n   fail-closed gate; they are rare and already hand-applied. Auto-apply of config is a documented v2 follow-up.\n4. **State/backoff unchanged.** `deployed-sha`/backoff/first-run-adopt as in v1; first run seeds the marker\n   from `/opt/rebar/.deployed_ref` if present (else the mirror tip), still WITHOUT deploying. A persistent\n   **git-fetch failure is instrumented** (`AUTODEPLOY_ERROR fetch_failed`) so a stalled mirror alarms.\n\n### systemd + installer + scope additions\n- **systemd fix:** `ExecStart=/opt/rebar/infra/scripts/autodeploy.sh` (not `/opt/rebar/src/…`),\n  `DEPLOY_REPO=/opt/rebar`, add `MIRROR_DIR=/var/lib/rebar/mirror`.\n- **`infra/scripts/install-autodeploy.sh`** (new; mirrors `install-observability.sh`): self-bootstraps the\n  mirror clone, installs the `.service`+`.timer` unit files, `daemon-reload`. **Ships the timer DISABLED**\n  (staged rollout: enable only after a manual dry-run passes).\n- The health check is a **liveness** probe (process up + `/health` 200), not a deep readiness check — the\n  AC wording is narrowed accordingly.\n\n### Additional acceptance criteria (box-adaptation)\n- [ ] autodeploy syncs source into the copy-based `/opt/rebar` via a self-bootstrapping regular mirror\n      clone (HTTPS-enforced) + `rsync --delete` with excludes; a live resync provably leaves\n      `infra/compose/.env` byte-identical and the `gerrit` container + Docker volumes untouched\n- [ ] v1 auto-applies review-bot ONLY; a replication/g2p/`refs/meta/config` change is detected + signalled\n      (`AUTODEPLOY_ERROR`), never auto-applied\n- [ ] `install-autodeploy.sh` installs units with the **timer disabled**; a manual dry-run\n      (`systemctl start rebar-autodeploy.service`) applies a real `main` advance end-to-end on the box\n      (review-bot rebuilt from synced source, health OK), evidenced by the deploy log SHA transition"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783107129602622001,"uuid":"5327aeec-b394-422b-b167-63d8c0b22330"}